title: Proton-induced cross-sections of nuclear reactions on lead up to 37 MeV

lead up to 37 MeV

x4codes.hlp: Institute for Nuclear Research (ATOMKI), Debrecen, Hungary

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.90, p.208 (2014)

x4freetext: Natural Pl metallic foils.
A stack of 12
identical groups of(Ho-Zr-Pb-Ti-Al) foil layers
containing Ho(26.2um), Zr(98.42um), Pb(15.74um) target
foils, Ti(12um) beam monitor foil and Al(156.6um) beam
energy degrader foils of natural isotopic composition
were irradiated with a proton beam of 37 MeV primary
energy and 146 nA intensity for 70 min.
Targets were counted four times after typical cooling
times of 1.3 h, 3.5 h, 97 h and 285 h .
The final beam current and energy
scale are based on the analysis of the cross section
data for the natTi(p,x)48V monitor reaction measured
simultaneously. with the investigated reactions

x4codes.shortRef: Rept: Nuclear Data Services (Doc. series of NDS), No.1211 (2001)

x4freetext: The uncertainty on the median energy in the
foils includes the cumulative effects of uncertainty of
incident beam energy, uncertainty of stopping power of
each foil due to thickness variation and  straggling
effects. Uncertainty of the primary incident beam was
+- 0.3MeV which increased up to +-0.75MeV in the last
Pb foil of the stack at LLN and 0.6 MeV at VUB.
The uncertainty on the cross section values
are estimated in the  standard way as the square root
of the quadratic summation of the independently
contributing parameters. Uncertainty of time parameters
is not included.
surface density of target nuclei(5%),
incident charged particle flux (7%),
statistical and peak fitting (1-15%)
The experimental data were compared to the
results of the theoretical model codes TENDL,
MENDL2p and EMPIRE.
The measured experimental data were compared to
those found in the literature.
Fitted excitation functions were used for
determination of integral physical yields.
Entry was checked by the corresponding author.
Data were taken from Table2 and
decay data from Table1 of the publication.
